        <section id="aviyon-origin">
            <h2>Aviyon: The Origin Story</h2>
            <p>Aviyon was conceived as a cloud-native platform to streamline development, deployment, and hosting. Drawing inspiration from Heroku’s deployment ease, Hostinger’s hosting flexibility, and Codeanywhere’s cloud IDE, Aviyon aimed to unify these into a modular, scalable ecosystem.</p>
            <h3>Vision and Pillars</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Modularity</strong>: Independent components (IDE, deployment, hosting, auth) connected via RESTful APIs.</li>
                <li><strong>Scalability</strong>: Built with Kotlin, Java, and Spring Boot for high concurrency.</li>
                <li><strong>User Experience</strong>: A PHP/Laravel frontend with Tailwind CSS for responsive design.</li>
                <li><strong>Extensibility</strong>: Plugin system for custom workflows.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Initial Tech Stack</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Backend</strong>: Spring Boot with Kotlin/Java, PostgreSQL, Redis, Kafka/RabbitMQ.</li>
                <li><strong>Frontend</strong>: Laravel 12.x, Blade templating, Tailwind CSS.</li>
                <li><strong>Orchestration</strong>: Kubernetes for container management.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This foundation enabled rapid iteration and set the stage for Aviyon’s cyberpunk transformation.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="aviyon-cyberpunk">
            <h2>Aviyon: Neon Code Rebellion</h2>
            <p>Aviyon transcended its utilitarian roots to become a cyberpunk-inspired coding platform, immersing developers in a dystopian world of neon-lit challenges and underground collaboration.</p>
            <h3>Core Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Neon UI</strong>: A dark, vibrant interface with purple, cyan, and white hues.</li>
                <li><strong>Cyber Missions</strong>: Coding tutorials styled as high-stakes hacking quests.</li>
                <li><strong>Code Crucible</strong>: Monaco-based cloud IDE with syntax highlighting.</li>
                <li><strong>Hacker Sync</strong>: Real-time multiplayer coding (in development).</li>
                <li><strong>Fortified Auth</strong>: JWT-based security via Spring Boot.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Technical Evolution</h3>
            <p>The frontend adopted Laravel 12.x with Vite for fast asset bundling, while the backend leveraged Spring Boot 3.2.0 and Kotlin 1.9.0. The file structure includes:</p>
            <pre>
frontend/
├── app/
├── resources/
│   ├── css/
│   ├── js/
│   ├── views/
├── routes/
├── public/
│   ├── build/
core/
├── auth/
├── logging/
├── config/
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section id="nimbus-ai">
            <h2>Nimbus.ai: Pinnacle of Intelligence</h2>
            <p>Nimbus.ai is Aviyon’s AI-driven evolution, aiming for ASI and AGI to address global challenges. Inspired by *Ghost in the Shell* and the Thunderhead from *Scythe*, it seeks to replicate consciousness and merge human minds with the cloud.</p>
            <h3>Objectives</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Solve intractable problems (e.g., climate change, disease).</li>
                <li>Develop sentient AI with empathy and autonomy.</li>
                <li>Enable brain-cloud interfaces for human-AI synergy.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Key Modules (Aviyon1.21)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Web Scanner</strong>: Crawls .edu/.gov/.org for credible data.</li>
                <li><strong>Knowledge Vault</strong>: Aggregates academic resources from MIT, Harvard, etc.</li>
                <li><strong>Truth Gauge</strong>: Evaluates information reliability.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.grammar1</strong>: Enhances writing with AI.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.code1</strong>: Analyzes GitHub/GitLab for coding insights.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.health1</strong>: Supports fitness and longevity (2045 Initiative).</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.business</strong>: Provides trading and investment strategies.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.planet</strong>: Drives sustainability efforts.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.nomad</strong>: Empowers nomadic lifestyles.</li>
                <li><strong>Aviyon.founder1</strong>: Chronicles Emmanuel Moore’s journey.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Nimbus Agents</h3>
            <p>Users can create up to five AI agents with custom roles, 3D avatars (Three.js), and exportable VRM models for kodoverse integration.</p>
            <h3>NFT Bazaar</h3>
            <p>Hosted on ICP with Motoko, the bazaar supports user-created NFTs, microtransactions (ICP, BTC, ETH, Stripe), and 3D gallery browsing.</p>
        </section>

